$ SAS automatic macro variables: sysscp and sysscpl

`&sysscp` and `&sysscpl` can be used to determine the operating system that a programm is running on.

This might be useful, for example, to determine if directories are → Companies-Products/SAS/macros/directory_seperator[seperated by a forward or backward slash].

